cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper introduces a generative model for documents that includes authorship information. This is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper applies the model to NIPS conference papers and CiteSeer abstracts, which are both relevant to these sub-categories.
